    public interface UiFeatureValue<VALUE>
extends UiFeature, AttributeWriteValueAdvanced<VALUE>
    This is the interface for the features of an object that has a value that can be changed programmatic as well as by the user (e.g. by typing in a text input field). Additionally, it allows to add and remove instances of UiHandlerEventValueChange.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
